<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="alarm-n">alarm <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'lɑːm/    美 /ə'lɑːrm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>警报 (器)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>raised</strong> / <strong>sounded the alarm</strong> as soon as I saw the smoke.
我一看见烟就发出了警报。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everyone fled from the building when the fire alarm sounded.
火警响起时，所有人都从大楼里逃了出来。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-alarm-clock">2.<strong>闹钟 (alarm clock)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>set the alarm</strong> for six 
把闹钟定在6点</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The <strong>alarm went off</strong> at five. 
闹钟在5点时响了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>惊恐；惊悚</strong></h4></div>